{"word":"ἐντρίβω","slug":"ἐντρίβω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐντρίβω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ψω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to rub in</i> or <i>into</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>ἐντρ. κόνδυλόν τινι</el> to give him a drubbing, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to rub</i> one <i>with</i> cosmetics, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to have</i> cosmetics <i>rubbed in, to be anointed, painted</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>to wear away by rubbing</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}